<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-107-124 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 967 514</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  July 12 1991 n1716* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EC labelling legislation helps Domino Printing to a 67% interimprofit rise. (European Community)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Domino Printing Sciences PLC (Finance).andO;Topic:     Ink-jet printersFinancial ReportEurope.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>EC LABELLING LEGISLATION HELPS DOMINO PRINTINGandM;TO A 67% INTERIM PROFIT RISEandM;Cambridge-based Domino Printing Sciences Plc has reported pre-tax profits forthe half year ending April 30 up 67% to #3.4m.andP;  Turnover was up 28% to#26.4m.andP;  Domino makes and markets industrial ink jet printers - a newlucrative printing market that has helped the company to achieve such healthyfigures has been the introduction of European legislation requiring &quot;use by&quot;and &quot;best before&quot; expiry dates on food.andP;  The company expects to continue tobenefit from new labelling laws.andP;  Domino has also recently signed a #1mprinting contract with The Daily Mirror Group.andP;  Chairman Gerald Dennis sayshe expects the growth achieved in the first half to continue into the secondhalf and noted the particular success of sales of the company's Codebox andSolo printers, which have been enhanced.andO;</TEXT></DOC>